<div class="xs-mb4 xs-pb4">

  <h2 class="bold xs-mb1">The Grid</h2>

  <p class="xs-mb1">For laying out pages, BuzzFeed uses a 12-column, fluid grid system (which can be made responsive using our breakpoint prefixes, we'll get to that later). In order to begin using the grid, wrap your main grid columns in a <code class="js-highlight">clearfix</code> container. You'll then need to use our <code class="js-highlight">col</code> and <code class="js-highlight">col-n</code> (where n is 1-12) classes to both float and then set the width of each column. Any given row can be made up of up to 12-columns, but can be less if you'd like!</p>

  <p class="xs-mb3">You can see an example below:</p>

  <div class="clearfix xs-mb3">
    <div class="col xs-col-3 xs-border-left xs-border-top xs-border-bottom xs-p1">col xs-col-3</div>
    <div class="col xs-col-4 xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
    <div class="col xs-col-5 xs-border-right xs-border-top xs-border-bottom xs-p1">col xs-col-5</div>
  </div>

  <p class="xs-mb1">And here's the code:</p>

  <pre><code class="html"><%='<div class="clearfix">'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-3">col xs-col-3</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-5">col xs-col-5</div>'%>
<%='</div>'%></code></pre>

</div>
<div class="xs-mb4 xs-pb4">

  <h2 class="bold xs-mb1">Gutters, Column Padding and Offsets</h2>

  <p class="xs-mb4">In order to add space around your columns, use our offset classes (which we'll get to momentarily) or our <a href="/layout/utilities">padding utility classes</a>  and wrap your column's content in a separate container. <b>Do not use margin or your grid will wrap.</b></p>

  <h3 class="bold xs-mb1">Automatic Gutters</h3>

  <p class="xs-mb3">The easiest way to set up column gutters is to add a <code class="js-highlight">gutters</code> class to your wrapping div, which results in a 1rem gutter between each column. Note that nesting columns do not receive automatic gutters, allowing you the flexibility to add them yourself with another <code class="js-highlight">gutters</code> class or with our padding utility classes:

  <div class="clearfix gutters xs-mb3">
    <div class="col xs-col-4">
      <div class="xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-4">
      <div class="xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-4">
      <div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="xs-mb1">Here's how it works in code</p>

   <pre class="xs-mb4"><code class="html"><%='<div class="clearfix gutters">'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">'%>
    <%='<div class="xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">'%>
    <%='<div class="xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4 xs-p1 xs-border rounded">col</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
<%='</div>'%></code></pre>


  <h3 class="bold xs-mb1">Using Padding to Space Columns</h3>

  <p class="xs-mb3">Here's an example of using <a href="/layout/utilities">padding utility classes</a> to space your grid columns:</p>

  <div class="clearfix xs-mb3">
    <div class="col xs-col-3 xs-pr1">
      <div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-3 xs-pr1</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-4 xs-pr2">
      <div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-4 xs-pr2</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-5">
      <div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-5</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="xs-mb1">Here's how it works in code:</p>

   <pre class="xs-mb4"><code class="html"><%='<div class="clearfix">'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-3 xs-pr1">'%>
    <%='<div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-3 xs-pr1</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-4 xs-pr2">'%>
    <%='<div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-4 xs-pr2</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-5">'%>
    <%='<div class="xs-border xs-p1">col xs-col-5</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
<%='</div>'%></code></pre>


  <h3 class="bold xs-mb1">Column Offsets</h3>

  <p class="xs-mb3">Use the <code class="js-highlight">offset-n</code> class (from 1-11) to offset a column div. Each step is one column width. So, for example, <code class="js-highlight">xs-offset-1</code> moves your div to the left by one column width, then <code class="js-highlight">xs-offset-2</code> moves it to column widths, and so on. Here's an example:</p>

  <div class="clearfix xs-mb2">
    <div class="col xs-col-8 xs-offset-2 xs-border xs-p1">xs-col-8 xs-offset-2</div>
  </div>
  <div class="clearfix">
    <div class="col xs-col-3 xs-offset-2 xs-border xs-p1">xs-col-3 xs-offset-2</div>
    <div class="col xs-col-3 xs-offset-2 xs-border xs-p1">xs-col-3 xs-offset-2</div>
  </div>


</div>
<div class="xs-mb4 xs-pb4">

  <h2 class="bold xs-mb1">Nesting Columns</h2>

  <p class="xs-mb3">Since our grid is percentage-based, it can be nested within itself. When you nest a new grid, the columns are sized relative to the parent. Like so:</p>

  <div class="clearfix xs-mb3">
    <div class="col xs-col-6 xs-border-left xs-border-top xs-border-bottom xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-mb1">col xs-col-6</p>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-border-right xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-border-right xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-6 xs-border xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-mb1">col xs-col-6</p>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-border-right xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-border-right xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
      <div class="col xs-col-4 fill-yellow xs-p1">col xs-col-4</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="xs-mb1">And the code:</p>

  <pre><code class="html"><%='<div class="clearfix">'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-6">'%>
    <%='<p>col xs-col-6</p>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="col xs-col-6">'%>
    <%='<p>col xs-col-6</p>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
    <%='<div class="col xs-col-4">col xs-col-4</div>'%>
  <%='</div>'%>
<%='</div>'%></code></pre>

</div>

<div class="xs-mb4 clearfix">
  <h2 class="bold xs-mb1">Responsive Grid</h2>

  <p class="xs-mb3">The responsive grid is implemented by adding <a href="/layout/responsive">breakpoint prefixes</a> to the column classes. For each breakpoint that you need a new column-width for, you'll add that class to the element. For example, if a div should take up the full width, <code class="js-highlight">xs-col-12</code>, at the smallest breakpoint, and half width, <code class="js-highlight">xs-col-6</code>, at the medium breakpoint, the div would get classes <code class="js-highlight">xs-col-12</code> <code class="js-highlight">md-col-6.</code> <b>Resize your browser to see the full effect below:</b></p>

  <div class="clearfix xs-mb3">
    <div class="col xs-col-12 sm-col-12 md-col-6 lg-col-3 xs-border xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-show sm-hide">xs-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide sm-show md-hide">sm-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide md-show lg-hide">md-col-6</p>
      <p class="xs-hide lg-show">lg-col-3</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-12 md-col-6 lg-col-3 xs-border xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-show sm-hide">xs-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide sm-show md-hide">sm-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide md-show lg-hide">md-col-6</p>
      <p class="xs-hide lg-show">lg-col-3</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-12 md-col-6 lg-col-3 xs-border xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-show sm-hide">xs-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide sm-show md-hide">sm-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide md-show lg-hide">md-col-6</p>
      <p class="xs-hide lg-show">lg-col-3</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col xs-col-12 md-col-6 lg-col-3 xs-border xs-p1">
      <p class="xs-show sm-hide">xs-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide sm-show md-hide">sm-col-12</p>
      <p class="xs-hide md-show lg-hide">md-col-6</p>
      <p class="xs-hide lg-show">lg-col-3</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="xs-mb1">Here's how it's done:</p>

  <pre><code class="html"><%= '<div class="clearfix xs-mb3">' %>
